# Airtable Configuration (set these in Vercel dashboard under Environment Variables)
#
# 1. Create a free account at https://airtable.com
# 2. Create a base called "Wedding RSVP"
# 3. Create a table called "RSVP_Responses" with fields:
#    - Name (Single line text)
#    - Email (Email)
#    - Phone (Phone number)
#    - Guest_Count (Number)
#    - Event (Single select: Engagement, Shaadi, Valima)
#    - Side (Single line text)
#    - Group_Name (Single line text)
#    - Message (Long text) — optional
#    - Submitted_At (Created time) — auto-generated
# 4. Create a Personal Access Token at https://airtable.com/create/tokens
#    - Add scopes: data.records:read, data.records:write
#    - Add access to your "Wedding RSVP" base
# 5. Get your Base ID from the API documentation or your base URL
#
# IMPORTANT: These are server-side variables (used by Vercel serverless functions).
# Do NOT prefix with VITE_ — they should NOT be exposed to the browser.

AIRTABLE_API_KEY=your_personal_access_token_here
AIRTABLE_BASE_ID=your_base_id_here
AIRTABLE_TABLE_NAME=RSVP_Responses
